-6}}\n* Truong, Monique. ''The book of salt'', Boston: Houghton Mifflin Company, 2003. A novel about a young Vietnamese cook who worked in Stein's Montparnasse-household.\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wiktionary|there is no there there}}\n{{Portal|Biography|LGBT}}\n{{Sister project links |wikt=no |commons= |b= |n= |q= |s=Author:Gertrude Stein |v= |species=no }}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=Stein,+Gertrude | name=Gertrude Stein}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Gertrude Stein}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=2294}}\n* {{Citation | url = http://beinecke.library.yale.edu/digitallibrary/stein.html | contribution = Gertrude Stein and Alice B. Toklas Papers | title = Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library | publisher = Yale University | access-date = 2009-07-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110812102125/http://beinecke.library.yale.edu/digitallibrary/stein.html | archive-date = 2011-08-12 | url-status=dead }}.\n* {{Citation | url = http://xroads.virginia.edu/~HYPER2/stein/stein.html | title = Three Lives | publisher = American Studies at the University of Virginia | access-date = 2009-10-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20091113013738/http://xroads.virginia.edu/~HYPER2/stein/stein.html | archive-date = 2009-11-13 | url-status = dead }}.\n* {{Citation | url = http://writing.upenn.edu/pennsound/x/Stein.html | title = Complete, authorized audio recordings at PennSound | access-date = 2013-07-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130704180842/http://writing.upenn.edu/pennsound/x/Stein.html | archive-date = 2013-07-04 | url-status = dead }}\n* {{Citation | url = http://www.pbase.com/empirebuilder/image/58373068 | title = Allegheny City (Deutschtown), Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania | format = birth placard | publisher = PBase | access-date = 2007-08-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090126085624/http://www.pbase.com/empirebuilder/image/58373068 | archive-date = 2009-01-26 | url-status = dead }}.\n* {{Citation