odgeAtVillaCuronia | title = Gertrude Stein, Gradually}}; readings from ''Autobiography of Alice B. Toklas'', ''Bee Time Vine'', and more. Includes excerpts from ''Patriarchal Poetry'' and layered-voice readings.\n* {{Citation | url = http://www.nyc-arts.org/showclips/show/id/70 | archive-url = https://archive.today/20130415163758/http://www.nyc-arts.org/showclips/show/id/70 | url-status = dead | archive-date = 2013-04-15 | publisher = NYC-Arts | format = profile | title = \"The Steins Collect: Matisse, Picasso, and the Parisian Avant Garde\" at the Metropolitan Museum of Art | date = 2009-04-02 }}.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130730055758/http://www.brainpickings.org/index.php/2013/01/23/gertrude-stein-the-making-of-americans/ Gertrude Stein Reads from ''The Making of Americans''] a rare recording made in 1934 and 1935\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Jack Crawford (tennis)|Jack Crawford]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of covers of Time magazine (1930s)|Cover of ''Time'' magazine]] |years=11 September 1933}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[George F. Zook]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Gertrude Stein}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stein, Gertrude}}\n[[Category:Gertrude Stein]]\n[[Category:1874 births]]\n[[Category:1946 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century American women]]\n[[Category:20th-century American dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:20th-century American novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century American poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:Jewish women writers]]\n[[Category:American autobiographers]]\n[[Category:Jewish feminists]]\n[[Category:American feminist writers]]\n[[Category:Jewish American poets]]\n[[Category:American opera librettists]]\n[[Category:Modern art]]\n[[Category:Modernist theatre]]\n[[Category:American modernist poets]]\n[[Category:Modernist women writers]]\n[[Category:Cubism]]\n[[Category:Johns Hopkins University alumni]]\n[[Category:Radcliffe College alumni]]\n[[Category:Lesbian writers]]\n[[Category:Lesbian feminists]]\n[[Category:LGBT writers from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT Jews]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in France]]\n[[Category:French Jews]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in Austria]]\n[[Category:American people of German-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Writers from Oakland, California]]\n[[Category:Writers from Pittsburgh]]\n[[Category:Deaths from stomach cancer]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in France]]\n[[Category:Burials at P\u00e8re Lachaise Cemetery]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Modernist writers]]\n[[Category:LGBT dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:LGBT poets]]\n[[Category:American women poets]]\n[[Category:Women autobiographers]]\n[[Category:Self-published authors]]\n[[Category:Women opera librettists]]\n[[Category:People from Baltimore]]\n[[Category:Novelists from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:American women non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American art collectors]]\n[[Category:LGBT memoirists]]\n[[Category:American art patrons]]\n", "name_user": "Nihiltres", "label": "safe", "comment": "Hyphenated ISBNs", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gertrude_Stein"}
{"title_page": "2006\u201307 Macedonian First Football League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition      = Macedonian First League\n| season           = 2006\u201307\n| winners          = [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]<br />2nd domestic title\n| relegated        = [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica Shtip]]<br />[[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]]\n| continentalcup1  = [[2007\u201308 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[2007\u201308 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]]<br />[[FK Vardar|Vardar]]\n| continentalcup3  = [[2007 UEFA Intertoto Cup|Intertoto Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija GP]]\n| league topscorer = [[Boban Jan\u010devski|Boban Janchevski]]<br />(26 goals)\n| dates            = 6 August 2006 \u2013<br /> 27 May 2007\n| biggest home win = [[FK Vardar|Vardar]] 10\u20130 [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]]\n| biggest away win = [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] 0\u20135<br>[[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija GP]]<br>''2 matches''<br />[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica]] 0\u20135 [[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]]\n| highest scoring  = [[FK Vardar|Vardar]] 10\u20130 [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]]\n| matches          = 198\n| total goals      = 604\n| prevseason = [[2005\u201306 Macedonian First Football League|2005\u201306]]\n| nextseason = [[2007\u201308 Macedonian First Football League|2007\u201308]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2006\u201307 Macedonian First League''' was the 15th season of the [[Macedonian First Football League]], the highest [[Association football|football]] league of [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]. The first matches of the season were played on 6 August 2006 and the last on 27 May 2007. [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]] were the defending champions, having won their second title. The 2006-07 champions were [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] who had won their second title.\n\n== Promotion and relegation ==\n{|style=\"border:0;width:69%;\"\n|-style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n|\n; At the start of the 2006\u201307 season\nPromoted from [[2005\u201306 Macedonian Second Football League|2005\u201306 Second League]]\n* [[FK Pelister|Pelister]] (Winners)\n* [[FK Napredok|Napredok]] (Runners-up)\nRelegated to [[2006\u201307 Macedonian Second Football League|2006\u201307 Second League]]\n* [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica 55]] (11th)\n* [[FK Belasica|Belasica]] (12th)\n\n|\n; At the end of the 2006\u201307 season\nPromoted from [[2006\u201307 Macedonian Second Football League|2006\u201307 Second League]]\n* [[KF Milano Kumanov\u00eb|Milano]] (Winners)\n* [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica 55]] (Runners-up)\nRelegated to [[2007\u201308 Macedonian Second Football League|2007\u201308 Second League]]\n* [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica Kraun]] (11th)\n* [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] (12th)\n|}\n\n== Participating teams ==\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=400|caption=Location of teams in '''2006\u201307 Macedonian First League'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=21.433333 |label='''Skopje'''  |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.130533 |long=21.721219 |label=[[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.517778 |long=20.965556 |label=[[FK Napredok|Napredok]]<br>[[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.031944 |long=21.334722 |label=[[FK Pelister|Pelister]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.35     |long=21.55     |label=[[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.032777 |long=21        |label=[[KF Renova|Renova]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.733333 