ntinentalcup3  = [[2007 UEFA Intertoto Cup|Intertoto Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija GP]]\n| league topscorer = [[Boban Jan\u010devski|Boban Janchevski]]<br />(26 goals)\n| dates            = 6 August 2006 \u2013<br /> 27 May 2007\n| biggest home win = [[FK Vardar|Vardar]] 10\u20130 [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]]\n| biggest away win = [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] 0\u20135<br>[[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija GP]]<br>''2 matches''<br />[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica]] 0\u20135 [[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]]\n| highest scoring  = [[FK Vardar|Vardar]] 10\u20130 [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]]\n| matches          = 198\n| total goals      = 604\n| prevseason = [[2005\u201306 Macedonian First Football League|2005\u201306]]\n| nextseason = [[2007\u201308 Macedonian First Football League|2007\u201308]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2006\u201307 Macedonian First League''' was the 15th season of the [[Macedonian First Football League]], the highest [[Association football|football]] league of [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]. The first matches of the season were played on 6 August 2006 and the last on 27 May 2007. [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]] were the defending champions, having won their second title. The 2006-07 champions were [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] who had won their second title.\n\n== Promotion and relegation ==\n{|style=\"border:0;width:69%;\"\n|-style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n|\n; At the start of the 2006\u201307 season\nPromoted from [[2005\u201306 Macedonian Second Football League|2005\u201306 Second League]]\n* [[FK Pelister|Pelister]] (Winners)\n* [[FK Napredok|Napredok]] (Runners-up)\nRelegated to [[2006\u201307 Macedonian Second Football League|2006\u201307 Second League]]\n* [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica 55]] (11th)\n* [[FK Belasica|Belasica]] (12th)\n\n|\n; At the end of the 2006\u201307 season\nPromoted from [[2006\u201307 Macedonian Second Football League|2006\u201307 Second League]]\n* [[KF Milano Kumanov\u00eb|Milano]] (Winners)\n* [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica 55]] (Runners-up)\nRelegated to [[2007\u201308 Macedonian Second Football League|2007\u201308 Second League]]\n* [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica Kraun]] (11th)\n* [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] (12th)\n|}\n\n== Participating teams ==\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=400|caption=Location of teams in '''2006\u201307 Macedonian First League'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=21.433333 |label='''Skopje'''  |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.130533 |long=21.721219 |label=[[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.517778 |long=20.965556 |label=[[FK Napredok|Napredok]]<br>[[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.031944 |long=21.334722 |label=[[FK Pelister|Pelister]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.35     |long=21.55     |label=[[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.032777 |long=21        |label=[[KF Renova|Renova]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.733333 |long=22.183333 |label=[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.066667 |long=22.183333 |label=[[FK Sileks|Sileks]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=20.966666 |label=[[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]] |position=bottom}}\n<!--HIDDEN MARKER FOR SKOPJE CLUBS (UPPER RIGHT CORNER)-->\n{{Location map~ |Republic of Macedonia|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png|lat=42.44 |long=23.2 |label='''Skopje&nbsp;clubs:'''|position=left |outside  = 1 <!--Suppress warning category-->}}\n{{Location map~ |Republic of Macedonia|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png|lat=42.36 |long=23.2 |label=[[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija]]<br>[[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]]<br>[[FK Vardar|Vardar]] |position=left |outside  = 1 <!--Suppress warning category-->}}\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Club\n! City\n! Stadium\n! Capacity\n|-\n| [[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]]\n| [[Kumanovo]]\n| [[Gradski Stadium Kumanovo|Gradski stadion Kumanovo]]\n| 7,000\n|-\n| [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica Kraun]]\n| [[\u0160tip|Shtip]]\n| [[Gradski stadion \u0160tip|Gradski stadion Shtip]]\n| 4,000\n|-\n| [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija GP]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[Gjor\u010de Petrov Stadium|Stadion Gjorche Petrov]]\n| 3,000\n|-\n| [[FK Napredok|Napredok]]\n| [[Ki\u010devo|Kichevo]]\n| [[Gradski stadion Ki\u010devo|Gradski stadion Kichevo]]\n| 5,000\n|-\n| [[FK Pelister|Pelister]]\n| [[Bitola]]\n| [[Stadion Tumbe Kafe]]\n| 8,000\n|-\n| [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]\n| [[Prilep]]\n| [[Stadion Goce Del\u010dev|Stadion Goce Delchev]]\n| 15,000\n|-\n| [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki Kometal]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[To\u0161e Proeski Arena|Gradski stadion Skopje]]\n| 18,104\n|-\n| [[KF Renova|Renova]]\n| [[D\u017eep\u010di\u0161te|Djepchishte]]\n| [[Ecolog Arena|Gradski stadion Tetovo]]\n| 15,000\n|-\n| [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija 79]]\n| [[Tetovo]]\n| Gradski stadion Tetovo\n| 15,000\n|-\n| [[FK Sileks|Sileks]]\n| [[Kratovo, North Macedonia|Kratovo]]\n| [[Gradski stadion Kratovo|Stadion Sileks]]\n| 5,000\n|-\n| [[FK Vardar|Vardar]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| Gradski stadion Skopje\n| 18,104\n|-\n| [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]]\n| Kichevo\n| Gradski stadion Kichevo\n| 5,000\n|}\n\n==League table==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|source=[http://macedonianfootball.com/1-mfl-2006-07-final-standings/ MacedonianFootball.com], [http://www.rsssf.com/tablesf/fyrom07.html RSSSF.com]\n\n<!--Update team positions here-->\n|team1=POB |team2=RAB |team3=MGP |team4=VAR |team5=REN |team6=PEL |team7=NAP |team8=BAS |team9=SIL |team10=SHK |team11=