ints; 2) Goal difference; 3) Goals scored; 4) Head-to-head points; 5) Head-to-head goal difference; 6) Head-to-head away goals scored (only if two teams); 7) Head-to-head goals scored; 8) Draw; 9) Play-off. (Note: Criteria 2, 3 and 8 is only used if not deciding Champion, teams for UEFA competitions or relegation).\n\n<!--Qualification and relegation column definitions-->\n|res_col_header=QR\n|col_CL1Q=green1 |text_CL1Q=Qualification for the [[2007\u201308 UEFA Champions League#First qualifying round|Champions League first qualifying round]]\n|col_UC1Q=blue1  |text_UC1Q=Qualification for the [[2007\u201308 UEFA Cup#First qualifying round|UEFA Cup first qualifying round]]\n|col_UC1CQ=blue1  |text_UC1CQ=Qualification for the [[2007\u201308 UEFA Cup#First qualifying round|UEFA Cup first qualifying round]]\n|col_IC1=#ccccff |text_IC1=Qualification for the [[2007 UEFA Intertoto Cup#First round|Intertoto Cup first round]]\n|col_RPO=red2 |text_RPO=Qualification for the [[2006\u201307 Macedonian First Football League#Relegation play-offs|relegation play-offs]]\n|col_REL=red1    |text_REL=Relegation to the [[2007\u201308 Macedonian Second Football League|Macedonian Second Football League]]\n|note_res_UC1CQ=[[FK Vardar|Vardar]] qualified for the [[2007\u201308 UEFA Cup#First qualifying round|UEFA Cup first qualifying round]] by winning the [[2006\u201307 Macedonian Football Cup]].\n\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n== Results ==\nEvery team will play three times against each other team for a total of 33 matches. The first 22 matchdays will consist of a regular double round-robin schedule. The league standings at this point will then be used to determine the games for the last 11 matchdays.\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Matches 1\u201322===\n{{#invoke:sports results|main\n|matches_style=FBR\n|team1=BAS|team2=BRE|team3=MGP|team4=NAP|team5=PEL\n|team6=POB|team7=RAB|team8=REN|team9=SKE|team10=SIL\n|team11=VAR|team12=VLZ\n\n|name_BAS=[[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]]\n|match_BAS_B