tball (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2005-06 First Macedonian Football League}}\n[[Category:2005\u201306 in European association football leagues|Macedonia]]\n[[Category:2005\u201306 in Republic of Macedonia football|1]]\n[[Category:Macedonian First Football League seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition      = Macedonian First League\n| season           = 2005\u201306\n| winners          = [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]]<br />2nd domestic title\n| relegated        = [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica]]<br />[[FK Belasica|Belasica]]\n| continentalcup1  = [[2006\u201307 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[2006\u201307 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija GP]]<br />[[FK Vardar|Vardar]]\n| continentalcup3  = [[2006 UEFA Intertoto Cup|Intertoto Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]\n| league topscorer = [[Stevica Risti\u0107]]<br />(27 goals)\n| dates            = 5 August 2005 \u2013<br /> 21 May 2006\n| biggest home win = [[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]] 6\u20130 [[FK Belasica|Belasica]]\n| biggest away win = [[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica]] 0\u20134 [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija]]\n| highest scoring  = [[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Belasica]] 4\u20136 [[FK Sileks|Sileks]]\n| matches          = 198\n| total goals      = 564\n| prevseason = [[2004\u201305 Macedonian First Football League|2004\u201305]]\n| nextseason = [[2006\u201307 Macedonian First Football League|2006\u201307]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2005\u201306 Macedonian First League''' was the 14th season of the [[Macedonian First Football League]], the highest [[Association football|football]] league of [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]. The first matches of the season were played on 5 August 2005 and the last on 21 May 2006. [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]] defended their championship title, having won their second title in a row.\n\n== Promotion and relegation ==\n{|style=\"border:0;width:69%;\"\n|-style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n|\n; At the start of the 2005\u201306 season\nPromoted from [[2004\u201305 Macedonian Second Football League|2004\u201305 Second League]]\n* [[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] (Winners)\n* [[KF Renova|Renova]] (Runners-up)\n* [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija Gjorche Petrov]] (Third placed; won play-off match)\nRelegated to [[2005\u201306 Macedonian Second Football League|2005\u201306 Second League]]\n* [[FK Mad\u017eari Solidarnost|Madjari Solidarnost]] (10th; lost play-off match)\n* [[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]] (11th)\n* [[FK Napredok|Napredok]] (12th)\n\n|\n; At the end of the 2005\u201306 season\nPromoted from [[2005\u201306 Macedonian Second Football League|2005\u201306 Second League]]\n* [[FK Pelister|Pelister]] (Winners)\n* [[FK Napredok|Napredok]] (Runners-up)\nRelegated to [[2006\u201307 Macedonian Second Football League|2006\u201307 Second League]]\n* [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica 55]] (11th)\n* [[FK Belasica|Belasica]] (12th)\n|}\n\n== Participating teams ==\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=400|caption=Location of teams in '''2005\u201306 Macedonian First League'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=21.433333 |label='''Skopje'''  |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.130533 |long=21.721219 |label=[[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.517778 |long=20.965556 |label=[[KF V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi 77|V\u00ebllaz\u00ebrimi]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.35     |long=21.55     |label=[[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.032777 |long=21        |label=[[KF Renova|Renova]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.733333 |long=22.183333 |label=[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip